Step 1: Determine the Net Profit from the Income Statement.  
• Net Profit = 1,105,265.77

Step 2: Identify the Total Assets in the Balance Sheet for the two dates.  
• Initial Total Assets = 13,000,000.00  
• Ending Total Assets = 15,653,266.97

Step 3: Calculate the Average Total Assets.  
• Average Total Assets = (Initial Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2  
• Average Total Assets = (13,000,000.00 + 15,653,266.97) / 2  
• Average Total Assets = 28,653,266.97 / 2 = 14,326,633.485

Step 4: Compute the Return on Assets (ROA) using the formula:  
  ROA = (Net Profit / Average Total Assets) × 100%

• ROA = (1,105,265.77 / 14,326,633.485) × 100%  
• ROA ≈ 0.0772 × 100%  
• ROA ≈ 7.72%

Thus, the Return on Assets is approximately 7.72%.
